+# Experiment Plan
+
+**Problem**: Determine whether `vLLM` on `DeepSeek-V2-Lite` matrix4 has optimization headroom for MoE load balancing, with **research question (2)** executed first and **research question (1)** kept as the next stage.
+**Method Thesis**: First build a directly comparable CV landscape over all existing runs and long-request candidate datasets; only after that, run the whole-model impact study on the datasets promoted by this landscape.
+**Date**: 2026-04-17
+
+## Claim Map
+
+| Claim | Why It Matters | Minimum Convincing Evidence | Linked Blocks |
+|-------|-----------------|-----------------------------|---------------|
+| C1 | Current `vLLM` vs `SGLang` conclusions are unstable unless all existing runs are recomputed under one unified CV metric. | A single saved table covering all recorder-compatible existing runs with the same formulas and the same dataset normalization. | B1 |
+| C2 | Some real downstream workloads, especially longer-request ones, can push `vLLM` into a higher-CV regime than the current `multifieldqa_en`, `2wikimqa`, `qasper` evidence. | At least one new `vLLM` run on an unrun long-request real benchmark lands in the top-CV band or exceeds a current comparator under the unified metric. | B2, B3 |
+
+## Anti-Claim To Rule Out
+
+- The apparent `vLLM` load-balancing headroom is only a metric artifact caused by inconsistent summaries across engines and datasets.
+- No real downstream benchmark that fits the current `vLLM` matrix4 setup reaches a meaningfully larger CV regime than the already measured workloads.
+
+## Paper Storyline
+
+- Main paper must prove:
+  - all existing evidence is re-scored under one unified metric
+  - the long-request candidate search is principled and reproducible
+  - at least one concrete `vLLM` long-request run either expands the observed CV frontier or fails to do so decisively
+  - only then does the project advance to the whole-model impact study
+- Appendix can support:
+  - synthetic `RULER` or kernel-CV stress tests
+  - non-recorder-compatible workloads after schema repair
+  - additional `LEval` subsets beyond the minimum set
+- Experiments intentionally cut from this stage:
+  - new balancing algorithms
+  - `RULER` as evidence for research question (2)
+  - full end-to-end policy tuning before the new CV frontier is known
+
+## Experiment Blocks
+
+### Block 1: Unified Existing-Run Recompute
+
+- Claim tested: `C1`
+- Why this block exists:
+  - It removes the current metric mismatch between `vLLM` and `SGLang`.
+  - It creates the baseline frontier that the new `vLLM` long-request runs must beat or match.
+- Dataset / split / task:
+  - Existing recorder-compatible runs only.
